President of Oodua Peoples Congress Reformed, Dare Adesope, has said those who attacked worshippers at St. Francis Catholic Church in Owo, Ondo State, committed a callous and wicked crime against humanity. Adesope regretted that the barbaric action against innocent people in broad day light and in such a brazen manner was without any basis. He urged the government to unmask those behind the killing.   Owo Church Attack: WHO pledges support for govt     Owo Church Attack: Adeboye prays against recurrence     Owo Church Attack: Victims to be buried soon   According to him, it is high time Southern governors empowered local security operatives, like members of OPC(R), to face terrorists threatening the region’s peace. “We are ready to work with other security operatives to save our communities from external terrorist,” he said. The OPC (R) President urged all the Southern governors to take security issue serious. Adesope called for a formidable strategy to be put in place in the Southwest so that the region’s security personnel could protect the residents in all situations.